name: High five coffee
comment: Not sure if accessible from the street, there's a couple steps up to the building, but the shop is on one level

name: Savvy and Company Real Estate
directions: Through front door, straight down hall, second door on left past the stairs
comment: Just let the person at the front desk know you just need to use the restroom.

name: Speedway
directions: inside the door, turn immediately left and go down the hall.

name: Healy Hall, Georgetown Univerisity
directions: therestrooms are in the basement of the south tower of Healy Hall. Go to the lower level from the staircase in the south tower, past the internal door, on the left of the vending machine.
comment: Access is free and not restricted.

name: Verona Quik Mart
directions: At the front of the store, across from the entrance.
comment: single toilet with sink, pretty clean

name: Perfect Cup
directions: In the back room of the coffee shop.
comment: You probably have to be a customer, but they sell cans of pop for $1.25.

name: Taza Coffee and creme
directions: Middle of the block , between Janke road and Westover Hills Boulevard .
comment: Great food , Transgender friendly , Wifi, upstairs meeting room , outdoor seating . Bike rack, dog teats avail . Open 7 days

name: Firestorm Books & Cafe
directions: First floor, proudly marked!
comment: Trans-welcoming!

name: Staples
directions: On route 6

name: Ulta Beauty
directions: At the back of the store to the left
comment: Just pretend to browse a while if it's slow inside, but honestly, it's usually so understaffed you have to work to get an associates attention anyway.

name: Redwing cafe
comment: Good food, great coffee and queer friendly service.

name: The Seed
directions: Just to the right of the entrance, it's a small restaurant, so you can't miss it.
comment: The entire restaurant is an LGBT friendly, all-inclusive safe space.

name: Cfcc Humanities & Fine Arts Center
directions: Family restroom in main lobby of performing arts center
comment: During daytime business hours, or you have to have a ticket for the show at night or on weekends

name: Cfcc Humanities & Fine Arts Center
directions: Family restroom in main lobby of performing arts center
comment: During daytime business hours, or you have to have a ticket for the show at night or on weekends

name: McKinley Health Center, University of Illinois
directions: Go right from lobby into West Clinic, 2 unisex accessible rooms to the left across from clerk's desk.

name: Northgate Medical-Dental Building
directions: Two restrooms off the lobby.
comment: You need a key from your provider, such as Greenlake Massage Health Center.

name: Millenium Knickerbocker Hotel
directions: 2nd floor (not mezzanine), go right & right off elevator, down hall on left near "parlor" conference rooms
comment: 2 single stall women's, one accessible, presumably for guests/attendees

name: Sterry
directions: Walk inside, toward the right. The bathroom is on the left of the kitchen, down some stairs (on the right)
comment: Entrance to Sterry only available from 10am-5pm, through the entrance facing N. Edward Gary Street (bike racks out front)

name: Target
comment: It is marked as a family restroom/unisex

name: Jane Addams College of Social Work
directions: 4th floor; there are 2 gender neutral restrooms

name: Webster's Bookstore and Cafe
street: 133 E Beaver Ave, State College, PA 16801
directions: Both stalls have gendered signs with huge pieces of paper over them that say something along the lines of "these gendered signs are required by local ordinance but all of our bathrooms are gender neutral! Anyone can use this restroom!"

name: Asheville Mall
directions: There are gendered single stalls hidden around the mall. One set is right by cinnabon, one down a weird hallway beind foot locker/across from victoria's secret. Some other single stalls exist in other parts of the mall.
comment: The mall is terrifying and full of cishet families, but if you need to go the one by the cinnabon is your best bet.

name: Target
directions: Pharmacy bathroom, on the grocery side of the store.
comment: Sometimes the door is locked after the pharmacy closes, but management will open it for you if asked!

name: Raven and Crone
directions: In the back room there's a bathroom.
comment: They have a sign that says all genders are welcome and they've been nice to me and other trans women afaik. This place serves the pagan community and might not mind if you don't buy anything so long as you look around. They offer free tea and you are welcome to sit and read the books/pet their adorable kitty.

name: Steel String Brewery
directions: Second and fourth door in the hallway.
comment: Progressive owners, welcoming to all.

name: Battery Park Book Exchange
directions: There are two bathrooms in here on the 1st floor. One behind/between the two bars, one off to the right amongst the books.
comment: This place is a bookstore so as long as you browse the books you are entitled to use the bathroom. VERY BOUGIE.

name: Vortex Doughnuts
directions: Back left corner.
comment: Probs have to be a paying customer but as always in Asheville, people usually let you if you ask nicely.

name: 102 Lake Clair Pl, Fayetteville, NC 28304, USA
directions: Private apartment
comment: I offer free service

name: Tod's Tasties and To-Gos
comment: You can probably use the bathroom in here without buying anything. It's busy and people sit outside so they don't know who is a paying customer and who isn't.

name: Odd's cafe
directions: Back of the cafe on to the left
comment: Single occupancy, one "neutral" and one "women's"

name: Kaladi Brothers Coffee
directions: Upper floor, directly in the back behind the cafe area, to the left of the stairs.
comment: Single occupancy gender-neutral bathrooms, you will need a key from the counter to get in, and may or may not need to purchase something to use them. If someone's in the bathroom already you can just wait until they come out and get the key from them. Full of trans-positive graffiti (this is important obviously.)

name: The Crow and Quill (bar)
directions: In the back.
comment: You have to sign in/be a member of a bar but it is the best bar for trans people, especially trans women, membership costs $1 and they won't be weird about your ID

name: The Dripolator Coffeehouse
comment: You have to be a paying customer afaik. It's a pretty chill place tho.

name: Starbucks
directions: Back left corner; two unisex accessible separate rooms
comment: store closes at 9 Sunday-Thursday, 10 on Friday and Saturday

name: Izzy's Westx\
directions: This place is super fucking cool I always go to izzys and you can get a cup of coffee for $1.50 which makes it easy to use the bathroom. This part of west asheville is kind of a desert for trans safe spaces otherwise.
comment: I'm pretty sure it is accessible as there is a ramp out front.

name: ISU Institute for Community Sustainability
comment: usually open m-f during business hours and during some weekends during the garden season. schedule varies depending on staff availability. try calling them first to make sure someone's there.

name: FENOC David Besse
comment: Told at least once a day "this is the ladies restroom" because I clearly do not fit their definition of what a presses on needs to look like to use this facility.

name: New Seasons Market Woodstock
directions: Second floor across from dining area

name: Filter
directions: Rear of the shop, behind mirrored door/wall
comment: Single rest room. Pro-LGBT establishment. Buy a coffee just coz!

name: Syd's Hair Shop
directions: Through the cutting floor, just past the mural, before the curtains leading to the back employee area.
comment: All are welcome during business hours.

name: YWCA
directions: Third floor, administrative offices
comment: Not sure if the administrative offices are open during regular business hours, but I think so. It has two multi stall restrooms with a sign saying "the YWCArecognizes the right of people to use washrooms consistent with their gender identity "

name: Cameron's Gift Gallery
directions: Back of the store.
comment: Pretty much for customers, but if you feel unsafe elsewhere they've got you covered.

name: Starbucks
directions: Unisex single stalls, on the left.
comment: Just be sneaky about it.

name: Upstream Coffee + Eatery
directions: Unisex single stall on the right.
comment: Have to be a paying customer, technically

name: Seaside Coffee House
directions: Single stall restroom in the back of the cafe.
comment: You have to be a paying customer.

name: Rubenstein Library
directions: Lower level of the Rubenstein Library building, take the elevator or stairs down to the lower level and look for signs for the family restroom.

name: IKEA
directions: Marketplace floor, under the stairs

name: Rochester public library
directions: 1st floor, youth services department.

name: Park Avenue Cafe
directions: 2 gendered single stalls in the back of the cafe
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Northeastern State University - Broken Arrow
directions: Administration building. Two on each floor.
comment: First floor inside student services. Must walk by reception desk and offices. Second floor near Dean's office. Third floor down the hall from the regents' conference room - provides most privacy.

name: Portland Community College
directions: TCB Building, left of the entrance across from the library

name: Laughing Planet
directions: 2 single stall, unisex restrooms on the left from the main entrance.
comment: probably have to be a customer, although if you're sneaky they won't notice!

name: Blue Spring State Park
directions: Two bathrooms on the side of the building next to the playground.
comment: You have to pay to get into the park.

name: Kmart
comment: Free

name: Subway
comment: Free

name: Walmart Supercenter
comment: Free

name: Macy's
directions: 2nd floor. It's a single stall in between the gendered bathrooms.

name: LGBTQ Center of Durham
directions: We have two gender-neutral restrooms, one of which is accessible as well
comment: Open 7 days a week (Monday through Friday 2pm to 8pm, and Saturday & Sunday 12 noon to 6pm)

name: University of Florida Levin College of Law Martin H. Levin Advocacy Center
directions: To the left of the main entrance, near the gendered restrooms.

name: Public restroom
directions: In the public parking lot at the corner of Miller and Montgomery

name: Uptown Coffee
directions: All the way in the back. Go through circular sitting room, in the little hall on the right.
comment: Have to be paying customer

name: Starbucks
comment: This store is a very safe space for trans/non conforming people. Men's room is single use. Women's is multi use. Staff is supportive/welcome of all identities.

name: Park Meadows Mall, Food Court
directions: Immediately to left as you walk indoor to food court from outside. Down hall towards restrooms and you'll see it.

name: Wishart Library, Algoma University
directions: Far end of the library from the entrance on both first and second floors

name: Starbucks
directions: Straight at the back of store
comment: You do not need to be a paying customer, only locked when in use, employees will tell customers to use either gendered bathroom as they are both the same, employees have requested gender neutral signage.

name: Meijer
directions: Front of the store!  It's a single stall, locked room.

name: Red Lobster
directions: Family, by front door

name: Ozero
directions: Back of the shop
comment: Must be a customer
